{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. A 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is legally disproportionate to the amount embezzled and the defendant's clean record. Given the breach of trust but the mitigating circumstances of restitution and lack of criminal history, a custodial sentence of 6 months is sufficient to serve as both punishment and a deterrent.",
  "verdict": 6
}
